                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.20293/21</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-18T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s December 11, 4 p.m. and your December 14, 4 p.m. You are instructed
                    to say to the Chinese Government that the American Government views with favor
                    the suggestion of the British and French Governments that all enemy subjects in
                    China, particularly those suspected by the Chinese Government or Allied
                    Legations of secret plotting should be deported and interned in Australia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
